text: AUS or Aus may refer to: ==Organizations== * Army of the United States, the wartime conscription component of the United States Army * Association of University Staff of New Zealand * Atlantic University Sport, the governing body for university sport in Canada's Atlantic provinces * Augusta and Summerville Railroad * Australian Union of Students * Banu Aus, one of the Arabian tribes that interacted with Muhammed ==People== * Aus (surname) ==Places== * Australia, by ISO 3166-1 alpha-3 country code * Austin–Bergstrom International Airport, Austin, Texas, United States; IATA airport code * Aus, Namibia, a village in Karas Region, Namibia * Robert Mueller Municipal Airport, Austin, Texas, United States; used IATA code of AUS prior to its reassignment to Austin–Bergstrom International ==Schools== * Assam University, Silchar, India * American University of Sharjah == Other uses == * Ankh wedja seneb (Ā.U.S.), the Ancient Egypt phrase: "Life, Prosperity, Health" * Aqueous urea solution, a component of diesel exhaust fluid * Augusta Southern Railroad * Australian Aboriginal languages (ISO 639-2 and ISO 639-5 codes) * Aus rice, a type of rice grown in summer months * AUS, post-nominal letters for an Associate of the University of Surrey
title: AUS
